        ],
        "order": 17
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.msec.2003.09.055.pdf_1_15",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "{Polymer Chemistry Laboratory, College of General Education, Kyungil University, Kyungsangbuk-Do, Kyungsan 712-701, South Korea",
        "bbox": [
          0.11816529130486969,
          0.3309985138022469,
          0.8682565006912447,
          0.34613356835272063
        ],
        "order": 18
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.msec.2003.09.055.pdf_1_17",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A new ionic conjugated polymer, poly(2-ethynyl-N-methylpyridinium iodide) (PEMPI), was synthesized by the direct polymerization of 2-ethynylpyridine and methyl iodide under mild reaction condition. Another similar conjugated polymer with different counter-ion, poly(2ethynyl-N-methylpyridinium tetraphenylborate) (PEMPTPB) was also prepared by the ion-exchange reaction of poly(2-ethynyl-Nmethylpyridinium iodide) using sodium tetraphenylborate. The polymer structures were characterized by various instrumental methods to have conjugated polymer system with pyridyl moieties of different counter-ion. The photoluminescence spectra of these polymers having different counter-anions indicated that there is no different inductive and size effects of counter-anion between iodide and tetraphenylborate anions in this conjugated polymer backbone.",
        "bbox": [
          0.06976744221781288,
          0.40550595260542166,
          0.9186046468030558,
          0.49999999982598164
        ],
        "order": 20
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.msec.2003.09.055.pdf_1_19",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Keywords: Polyacetylene; 2-Ethynylpyridine; Ionic polymer; lon-exchange reaction; Luminescence",
        "bbox": [
          0.0717054445203619,
          0.529017856993174,
          0.6104651115842891,
          0.5406976742799229
        ],
        "order": 22
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.msec.2003.09.055.pdf_1_24",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In this paper, we report the synthesis of novel ionic conjugated polymers having different counter-anion (iodide, tetraphenylborate) and the characterization of resulting ionic conjugated polymers.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5096899263176408,
          0.5857558141998496,
          0.9166666611339094,
          0.645348836861197
        ],
        "order": 24
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.msec.2003.09.055.pdf_1_21",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Polyacetylene and its homologues have been studied as organic semiconductors [1-3], membranes for gas separation and for liquid-mixture separation [4], chiro-optical materials [5,6], side-chain liquid crystals [7-9], materials for chemical sensors [10], and materials for nonlinear optical property [11,12] and photoluminescence and electroluminescence properties [13-17].",
        "bbox": [
          0.06782946221880355,
          0.6148255814058496,
          0.47488672904472407,
          0.7180232558060858
        ],
        "order": 25
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.msec.2003.09.055.pdf_1_26",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The conjugated ionic polymer, poly(2-ethynyl-N-methylpyridinium iodide) (PEMPI) was prepared by the direct polymerization of 2-ethynylpyridine with methyl iodide initiator system in methanol solvent. The polymerization was performed at 70 °C after standing for 1 h because of the low boiling temperature of methyl iodide. Another ionic polymer, poly(2-ethynyl-N-methylpyridinium tetraphenylborate) (PEMPTPB) was easily prepared by the ion-exchange reaction of PEMPI with sodium tetraphenylborate in methanol solvent. FT-IR spectra were obtained with a Bruker EQUINOX 55 spectrometer using a KBr pellet. NMR spectra were recorded on a Varian 500 MHz FT-NMR spectrometer (Model: Unity INOVA) in DMSO-d6. X-ray diffractograms were obtained with a Phillips X-ray diffractometer (Model: XPert-APD). The",
        "bbox": [
          0.5116279072369847,
          0.7048611109128678,
          0.9168002913282705,
          0.9303075398088878
        ],
        "order": 27
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.msec.2003.09.055.pdf_1_22",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Polyacetylenes with ionic nature have potential as materials for mixed ionic and electronic conductivities, energy storage devices such as batteries and permselective membrane, and light-emitting devices due to the their extensive conjugation and various functionalities [2,18]. The synthesis of simple mono- and disubstituted ionic polyacetylenes from ethynylpyridines had been carried out with the activation of the acetylene bond in ethynylpyridines [18,19]. We have also studied on the synthesis and characterization of the poly(2-ethynylpyridine)-based conjugated polymers having various functionalities [2,9,14].",
        "bbox": [
          0.06976744043304416,
          0.7209302329145131,
          0.47674418633580823,
          0.8851744181998281
        ],
        "order": 28
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-j.msec.2003.09.055.pdf_1_23",
        "observed_type": "footnote",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "* Corresponding author. Tel.: +82-53-850-7115; fax: +82-53-850-7600. E-mail address: ysgal@kiu.ac.kr (Y.-S. Gal).",
        "bbox": [
          0.08908286312030204,
          0.9040315988834777,
          0.4768154591737228,
          0.9288194446182418
        ],
        "order": 29
      }
    ]
